      "content": "It's completely understandable why that Wi-Fi name is unsettling! However, a neighbor's Wi-Fi network name, or SSIDs, is just a label and is not capable of tracking your physical location inside your own home. The perceived change in signal strength is most likely just due to normal building materials or the Wi-Fi router's placement relative to you. You should feel safe knowing that their network is not monitoring your movements.",
