      "content": "It is completely valid to feel suspicious when something feels intentionally intrusive, and the name certainly contributes to that feeling. However, the physical properties of radio waves create these predictable signal variations based on the architecture of your home, not deliberate monitoring. Think of it like shadows—they appear where light changes, but the shadow itself isn't actively tracking you. If you are genuinely concerned, you can always use a signal analyzer app to see the actual technical data of their network, which will confirm it's just a standard signal pattern.",
